<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="64" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 371.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-07-11"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 11, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 26th ultimo (No. 320) relative to the quotation of
                            stocks of the United States on the French bourse, which is approved. I
                            have also your No. 319 by the same mail.</p>
                        <p>Your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dayton</hi>, Esq.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>